import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='ignore')
    filtered_data = data[data['Entity'] == 'All natural disasters']
    
    plt.plot(filtered_data['Year'], filtered_data['Deaths'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the trend of deaths caused by natural disasters over time?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='ignore')
    data_2017 = data[data['Year'] == '2017-01-01']
    data_2017 = data_2017.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].sum().reset_index()
    data_2017 = data_2017.sort_values('Deaths', ascending=False)
    
    ax = data_2017.plot.bar(x='Entity', y='Deaths', legend=False)
    ax.set_ylabel('Deaths')
    ax.set_title('Which entity has the highest number of deaths caused by natural disasters?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    max_deaths = data_2017['Deaths'].max()
    max_entity = data_2017[data_2017['Deaths'] == max_deaths]['Entity'].values[0]
    ax.axhline(max_deaths, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Deaths: {max_deaths:.2f} ({max_entity})')
    ax.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    volcanic_data = data[data['Entity'] == 'Volcanic activity']
    plt.hist(volcanic_data['Deaths'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Deaths')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths caused by volcanic activity?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='ignore')
    wildfire_data = data[data['Entity'] == 'Wildfire']
    avg_deaths = wildfire_data.groupby('Year')['Deaths'].mean()
    
    plt.plot(avg_deaths.index, avg_deaths.values)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the average number of deaths caused by wildfires per year?")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
